Losing valuable minerals to tailings is a concern for every minerals plant, whether the result is lost profit or potential penalties from regulators. Consequently, it is of little surprise to see a growing level of interest in fine gravity separation technologies that can offer higher recoveries than traditional solutions. This article first appeared in Mining Review Africa Issue 4, 2019 and will be published in full on 3 May 2019 You can read the full digital magazine here or subscribe here to receive a print copy